{"author":{"id":"cc8322a500b8739c77faac347808f6026d9ccb7880d0aaa7ad76754163cd7fdb"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1782568927,"nonce":"sy5DW48CFEU+MI7ewvF/GHWFKjc=","kind":"plan","title":"Slice 1 — Content Evolution + Recall Implementation Plan"},{"type":3,"timestamp":1782568927,"nonce":"84CAW99uLYH6jbTwoYViLRhA+Bo=","body":"# Slice 1 — Content Evolution + Recall Implementation Plan\n\n\u003e **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (recommended) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.\n\n**Goal:** Make a kref entry editable and findable — derive titles on `add`, and add `kref update`, `kref edit`, `kref status`, and `kref list --search` — so the daily capture → recall → evolve loop works.\n\n**Architecture:** All capability logic stays in `internal/store` (which already has `Update(id, body, title)`); the new commands are thin `cmd/kref` adapters over it, rendering human/JSON via the existing `emit` seam. Title derivation is a pure helper in `internal/entry`. Recall is a linear filter added to the existing `store.List` — no index.\n\n**Tech Stack:** Go 1.26.4, cobra, ginkgo/gomega, git-bug `entity/dag`. No new dependencies.\n\n**Spec:** `docs/dev/specs/2026-06-20-unified-entry-model-design.md` §4.1 (Content + evolution) and §4.5 (Lifecycle).\n\n---\n\n## Content model decisions (locked)\n\n- **Body is the full markdown; the title is a derived projection of it.** Consistent with `ingest`, which stores the file content (H1 included) as the body and derives the title from the first H1.\n- **`add`:** `--title` overrides; otherwise the title is the first H1, else the first non-empty line, else error (an entry needs a title).\n- **`edit`/`update` title behavior uses `store.Update`'s existing semantics** (`title == \"\"` ⇒ leave title unchanged):\n  - `update --body X` changes the body only; `--title Y` also sets the title.\n  - `edit` re-derives the title from the body's **H1 only** — if the edited body has no H1, the title is left unchanged (no surprise retitle from a non-heading first line).\n\n## File Structure\n\n- **Modify** `internal/entry/operations.go` — add pure helpers `FirstHeading(body)` and `DeriveTitle(body)`.\n- **Modify** `internal/entry/operations_test.go` — unit tests for the helpers.\n- **Modify** `internal/store/store.go` — add `SetStatus(id, status)`; add `Search` to `ListFilter` and filter on it in `List`.\n- **Modify** `internal/store/store_test.go` — tests for `SetStatus` and search filtering.\n- **Modify** `cmd/kref/commands.go` — `add` title-optional; new `newUpdateCmd`, `newEditCmd`, `newStatusCmd`; `--search` flag on `list`; a `parseStatus` helper.\n- **Modify** `cmd/kref/main.go` — register the three new commands in the right groups.\n- **Modify** `cmd/kref/cli_test.go` — CLI specs for add-derivation, update, edit, status, search.\n- **Modify** `README.md`, `CHANGELOG.md` — document the new verbs and `--search`.\n\nSequencing: pure helpers (Task 1) → store methods (Tasks 2, 5) → CLI commands (Tasks 1, 3, 4, 5) → docs/verify (Task 6). The suite stays green at every commit.\n\n---\n\n## Task 1: Title derivation + `add` title-optional\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `internal/entry/operations.go`\n- Modify: `internal/entry/operations_test.go`\n- Modify: `cmd/kref/commands.go` (`newAddCmd`)\n- Modify: `cmd/kref/cli_test.go`\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Write the failing helper tests**\n\nAppend to `internal/entry/operations_test.go` (package `entry_test`, ginkgo — match the file's existing imports; it imports `. \"github.com/onsi/ginkgo/v2\"`, `. \"github.com/onsi/gomega\"`, and `\"github.com/riotbox/kref/internal/entry\"`):\n\n```go\nvar _ = Describe(\"DeriveTitle\", func() {\n\tIt(\"uses the first H1 heading\", func() {\n\t\tExpect(entry.DeriveTitle(\"# Auth flow\\n\\nbody\")).To(Equal(\"Auth flow\"))\n\t})\n\tIt(\"falls back to the first non-empty line when there is no H1\", func() {\n\t\tExpect(entry.DeriveTitle(\"\\n\\njust a line\\nmore\")).To(Equal(\"just a line\"))\n\t})\n\tIt(\"returns empty for empty content\", func() {\n\t\tExpect(entry.DeriveTitle(\"   \\n\\n\")).To(Equal(\"\"))\n\t})\n})\n\nvar _ = Describe(\"FirstHeading\", func() {\n\tIt(\"returns the H1 text\", func() {\n\t\tExpect(entry.FirstHeading(\"# Title\\n\\nx\")).To(Equal(\"Title\"))\n\t})\n\tIt(\"returns empty when there is no H1\", func() {\n\t\tExpect(entry.FirstHeading(\"no heading here\")).To(Equal(\"\"))\n\t})\n})\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Run the helper tests to verify they fail**\n\nRun: `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./internal/entry/ 2\u003e\u00261 | tail -5`\nExpected: FAIL — `undefined: entry.DeriveTitle` / `entry.FirstHeading`.\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Implement the helpers**\n\nAppend to `internal/entry/operations.go` (it already imports `\"strings\"`; if not, add it):\n\n```go\n// FirstHeading returns the text of the first markdown H1 (\"# ...\") line in\n// body, or \"\" if there is none.\nfunc FirstHeading(body string) string {\n\tfor _, line := range strings.Split(body, \"\\n\") {\n\t\ttrimmed := strings.TrimSpace(line)\n\t\tif strings.HasPrefix(trimmed, \"# \") {\n\t\t\treturn strings.TrimSpace(trimmed[2:])\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\treturn \"\"\n}\n\n// DeriveTitle picks a title from body: the first H1, else the first non-empty\n// line, else \"\". Used when `add` is called without an explicit --title.\nfunc DeriveTitle(body string) string {\n\tif h := FirstHeading(body); h != \"\" {\n\t\treturn h\n\t}\n\tfor _, line := range strings.Split(body, \"\\n\") {\n\t\tif trimmed := strings.TrimSpace(line); trimmed != \"\" {\n\t\t\treturn trimmed\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\treturn \"\"\n}\n```\n\nAdd `\"strings\"` to `operations.go`'s import block (it currently imports only `\"fmt\"`).\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Run the helper tests to verify they pass**\n\nRun: `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./internal/entry/ 2\u003e\u00261 | tail -5`\nExpected: PASS.\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Write the failing `add` CLI spec**\n\nAppend to `cmd/kref/cli_test.go`:\n\n```go\nvar _ = Describe(\"add title derivation\", func() {\n\tIt(\"derives the title from the body's H1 when --title is omitted\", func() {\n\t\tdir := gitRepo()\n\t\trun(\"--dir\", dir, \"init\", \"--name\", \"T\", \"--email\", \"t@e.com\")\n\t\trun(\"--dir\", dir, \"add\", \"--body\", \"# Derived heading\\n\\nprose\")\n\t\tout := run(\"--dir\", dir, \"list\")\n\t\tExpect(out).To(ContainSubstring(\"Derived heading\"))\n\t})\n\tIt(\"errors when neither --title nor a usable body is given\", func() {\n\t\tdir := gitRepo()\n\t\trun(\"--dir\", dir, \"init\", \"--name\", \"T\", \"--email\", \"t@e.com\")\n\t\tvar buf bytes.Buffer\n\t\tc := newRootCmd()\n\t\tc.SetOut(\u0026buf)\n\t\tc.SetErr(\u0026buf)\n\t\tc.SetArgs([]string{\"--dir\", dir, \"add\", \"--body\", \"   \"})\n\t\tExpect(c.Execute()).To(HaveOccurred())\n\t})\n})\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 6: Run the `add` spec to verify it fails**\n\nRun: `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./cmd/kref/ 2\u003e\u00261 | tail -10`\nExpected: FAIL — `add` currently requires `--title` (MarkFlagRequired), so the first spec errors instead of deriving.\n\n- [ ] **Step 7: Make `add` derive the title**\n\nIn `cmd/kref/commands.go` `newAddCmd`, (a) delete the line `_ = c.MarkFlagRequired(\"title\")`, and (b) insert title derivation immediately before the `id, err := s.Add(...)` call:\n\n```go\n\t\t\tif title == \"\" {\n\t\t\t\ttitle = entry.DeriveTitle(body)\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tif title == \"\" {\n\t\t\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"provide --title, or a --body with a heading or text to derive one from\")\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tid, err := s.Add(t, kind, title, body)\n```\n\n(`entry` and `fmt` are already imported in `commands.go`.)\n\n- [ ] **Step 8: Run the suite to verify it passes**\n\nRun: `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./cmd/kref/ ./internal/entry/ 2\u003e\u00261 | tail -8`\nExpected: PASS.\n\n- [ ] **Step 9: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add internal/entry/operations.go internal/entry/operations_test.go cmd/kref/commands.go cmd/kref/cli_test.go\ngit commit -m \"feat(add): derive title from body H1/first line when --title omitted\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 2: `kref status` (set lifecycle status)\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `internal/store/store.go` (add `SetStatus`)\n- Modify: `internal/store/store_test.go`\n- Modify: `cmd/kref/commands.go` (`parseStatus`, `newStatusCmd`)\n- Modify: `cmd/kref/main.go` (register the command)\n- Modify: `cmd/kref/cli_test.go`\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Write the failing store test**\n\nAppend to `internal/store/store_test.go` (package `store`, ginkgo — it has a `gitRepo()` helper and uses `Init`). Mirror the existing `Tombstone`/`Restore` test style:\n\n```go\nvar _ = Describe(\"Store SetStatus\", func() {\n\tIt(\"changes an entry's status\", func() {\n\t\tdir := gitRepo()\n\t\ts, err := Init(dir, \"Tester\", \"t@e.com\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tDeferCleanup(func() { _ = s.Close() })\n\t\tid, err := s.Add(entry.TierShared, \"spec\", \"T\", \"b\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\n\t\tExpect(s.SetStatus(id, \"accepted\")).To(Succeed())\n\t\tsnap, err := s.Get(id)\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(snap.Status).To(Equal(\"accepted\"))\n\t})\n\tIt(\"errors for an unknown id\", func() {\n\t\tdir := gitRepo()\n\t\ts, err := Init(dir, \"Tester\", \"t@e.com\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tDeferCleanup(func() { _ = s.Close() })\n\t\tExpect(s.SetStatus(entity.Id(\"deadbeef\"), \"accepted\")).To(HaveOccurred())\n\t})\n})\n```\n\nEnsure `store_test.go` imports `\"github.com/git-bug/git-bug/entity\"` and `\"github.com/riotbox/kref/internal/entry\"` (add any missing).\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Run the store test to verify it fails**\n\nRun: `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./internal/store/ 2\u003e\u00261 | tail -6`\nExpected: FAIL — `s.SetStatus undefined`.\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Implement `store.SetStatus`**\n\nAdd to `internal/store/store.go`, mirroring `Tombstone` (place it next to `Tombstone`/`Restore`):\n\n```go\n// SetStatus appends a status change to an entry, searching all tiers.\nfunc (s *Store) SetStatus(id entity.Id, status string) error {\n\tfor _, t := range entry.AllTiers() {\n\t\te, err := entry.Read(s.repo, t, id)\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\tif entity.IsErrNotFound(err) {\n\t\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"read %s in tier %s: %w\", id, t, err)\n\t\t}\n\t\te.Append(entry.NewSetStatus(s.author, status))\n\t\treturn e.Commit(s.repo)\n\t}\n\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"entry %s not found\", id)\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Run the store test to verify it passes**\n\nRun: `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./internal/store/ 2\u003e\u00261 | tail -5`\nExpected: PASS.\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Write the failing CLI spec**\n\nAppend to `cmd/kref/cli_test.go`:\n\n```go\nvar _ = Describe(\"status command\", func() {\n\tIt(\"sets an entry's status and rejects unknown statuses\", func() {\n\t\tdir := gitRepo()\n\t\trun(\"--dir\", dir, \"init\", \"--name\", \"T\", \"--email\", \"t@e.com\")\n\t\tout := run(\"--dir\", dir, \"add\", \"--title\", \"S\", \"--body\", \"b\", \"--json\")\n\t\tvar added struct {\n\t\t\tID string `json:\"id\"`\n\t\t}\n\t\tExpect(json.Unmarshal([]byte(out), \u0026added)).To(Succeed())\n\n\t\tExpect(run(\"--dir\", dir, \"status\", added.ID, \"accepted\")).To(ContainSubstring(\"accepted\"))\n\t\tExpect(run(\"--dir\", dir, \"show\", added.ID, \"--json\")).To(ContainSubstring(`\"status\": \"accepted\"`))\n\n\t\tvar buf bytes.Buffer\n\t\tc := newRootCmd()\n\t\tc.SetOut(\u0026buf)\n\t\tc.SetErr(\u0026buf)\n\t\tc.SetArgs([]string{\"--dir\", dir, \"status\", added.ID, \"bogus\"})\n\t\tExpect(c.Execute()).To(HaveOccurred())\n\t})\n})\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 6: Run the spec to verify it fails**\n\nRun: `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./cmd/kref/ 2\u003e\u00261 | tail -8`\nExpected: FAIL — `unknown command \"status\"`.\n\n- [ ] **Step 7: Implement `parseStatus` and `newStatusCmd`**\n\nAdd to `cmd/kref/commands.go` (place `parseStatus` next to `parseTier`):\n\n```go\nfunc parseStatus(s string) (string, error) {\n\tswitch s {\n\tcase \"open\", \"active\", \"accepted\", \"superseded\":\n\t\treturn s, nil\n\tdefault:\n\t\treturn \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"invalid status %q (want open|active|accepted|superseded)\", s)\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc newStatusCmd(dir *string) *cobra.Command {\n\treturn \u0026cobra.Command{\n\t\tUse:   \"status \u003cid\u003e \u003cstatus\u003e\",\n\t\tShort: \"Set an entry's lifecycle status (open|active|accepted|superseded)\",\n\t\tArgs:  cobra.ExactArgs(2),\n\t\tRunE: func(cmd *cobra.Command, args []string) error {\n\t\t\tstatus, err := parseStatus(args[1])\n\t\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\t\treturn err\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\ts, err := store.Open(*dir)\n\t\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\t\treturn err\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tdefer s.Close()\n\t\t\tid, err := s.Resolve(args[0])\n\t\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\t\treturn err\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tif err := s.SetStatus(id, status); err != nil {\n\t\t\t\treturn err\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tsnap, err := s.Get(id)\n\t\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\t\treturn err\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\treturn emit(cmd,\n\t\t\t\tfunc(w io.Writer, color bool) {\n\t\t\t\t\tfmt.Fprintf(w, \"%s %s  %s\\n\", status, render.ShortID(id), render.Tier(snap.Tier, color))\n\t\t\t\t},\n\t\t\t\tmap[string]string{\"status\": status, \"id\": id.String()})\n\t\t},\n\t}\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 8: Register the command**\n\nIn `cmd/kref/main.go`, in the lifecycle group (next to `newRmCmd`/`newRestoreCmd`), add:\n\n```go\n\taddTo(\"lifecycle\", newStatusCmd(\u0026dir))\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 9: Run the suite to verify it passes**\n\nRun: `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./cmd/kref/ ./internal/store/ 2\u003e\u00261 | tail -8`\nExpected: PASS.\n\n- [ ] **Step 10: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add internal/store/store.go internal/store/store_test.go cmd/kref/commands.go cmd/kref/main.go cmd/kref/cli_test.go\ngit commit -m \"feat(status): kref status \u003cid\u003e \u003cstatus\u003e to set lifecycle status\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 3: `kref update` (non-interactive body/title update)\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `cmd/kref/commands.go` (`newUpdateCmd`)\n- Modify: `cmd/kref/main.go`\n- Modify: `cmd/kref/cli_test.go`\n\n`store.Update(id entity.Id, body, title string) error` already exists (it appends `SetBody` if the body changed and `SetTitle` if `title != \"\" \u0026\u0026 title != current`). `update` wraps it: body comes from `--body` or, if that flag is absent, from stdin.\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Write the failing CLI spec**\n\nAppend to `cmd/kref/cli_test.go`:\n\n```go\nvar _ = Describe(\"update command\", func() {\n\tadd := func(dir string) string {\n\t\tGinkgoHelper()\n\t\trun(\"--dir\", dir, \"init\", \"--name\", \"T\", \"--email\", \"t@e.com\")\n\t\tout := run(\"--dir\", dir, \"add\", \"--title\", \"Orig\", \"--body\", \"old body\", \"--json\")\n\t\tvar a struct {\n\t\t\tID string `json:\"id\"`\n\t\t}\n\t\tExpect(json.Unmarshal([]byte(out), \u0026a)).To(Succeed())\n\t\treturn a.ID\n\t}\n\n\tIt(\"replaces the body via --body\", func() {\n\t\tdir := gitRepo()\n\t\tid := add(dir)\n\t\tExpect(run(\"--dir\", dir, \"update\", id, \"--body\", \"new body\")).To(ContainSubstring(\"updated\"))\n\t\tExpect(run(\"--dir\", dir, \"show\", id)).To(ContainSubstring(\"new body\"))\n\t})\n\tIt(\"reads the body from stdin when --body is omitted\", func() {\n\t\tdir := gitRepo()\n\t\tid := add(dir)\n\t\trunIn(\"piped body\\n\", \"--dir\", dir, \"update\", id)\n\t\tExpect(run(\"--dir\", dir, \"show\", id)).To(ContainSubstring(\"piped body\"))\n\t})\n\tIt(\"also sets the title when --title is given\", func() {\n\t\tdir := gitRepo()\n\t\tid := add(dir)\n\t\trun(\"--dir\", dir, \"update\", id, \"--body\", \"x\", \"--title\", \"Renamed\")\n\t\tExpect(run(\"--dir\", dir, \"show\", id)).To(ContainSubstring(\"Renamed\"))\n\t})\n})\n```\n\n(`runIn(stdin, args...)` already exists in `cli_test.go`.)\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Run the spec to verify it fails**\n\nRun: `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./cmd/kref/ 2\u003e\u00261 | tail -8`\nExpected: FAIL — `unknown command \"update\"`.\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Implement `newUpdateCmd`**\n\nAdd to `cmd/kref/commands.go` (it already imports `\"io\"`; add `\"strings\"` only if not present — it is). Use `io.ReadAll` on `cmd.InOrStdin()`:\n\n```go\nfunc newUpdateCmd(dir *string) *cobra.Command {\n\tvar body, title string\n\tvar bodySet bool\n\tc := \u0026cobra.Command{\n\t\tUse:     \"update \u003cid\u003e\",\n\t\tAliases: []string{\"set\"},\n\t\tShort:   \"Update an entry's body (and optionally title); body from --body or stdin\",\n\t\tArgs:    cobra.ExactArgs(1),\n\t\tRunE: func(cmd *cobra.Command, args []string) error {\n\t\t\tbodySet = cmd.Flags().Changed(\"body\")\n\t\t\tif !bodySet {\n\t\t\t\traw, err := io.ReadAll(cmd.InOrStdin())\n\t\t\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\t\t\treturn err\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t\tbody = string(raw)\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tif strings.TrimSpace(body) == \"\" {\n\t\t\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"no body given (use --body or pipe content on stdin)\")\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\ts, err := store.Open(*dir)\n\t\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\t\treturn err\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tdefer s.Close()\n\t\t\tid, err := s.Resolve(args[0])\n\t\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\t\treturn err\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tif err := s.Update(id, body, title); err != nil {\n\t\t\t\treturn err\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tsnap, err := s.Get(id)\n\t\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\t\treturn err\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\treturn emit(cmd,\n\t\t\t\tfunc(w io.Writer, color bool) { render.Action(w, \"updated\", snap, color) },\n\t\t\t\tmap[string]string{\"status\": \"updated\", \"id\": id.String()})\n\t\t},\n\t}\n\tc.Flags().StringVar(\u0026body, \"body\", \"\", \"new body (if omitted, read from stdin)\")\n\tc.Flags().StringVar(\u0026title, \"title\", \"\", \"also set the title\")\n\treturn c\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Register the command**\n\nIn `cmd/kref/main.go`, in the core group (next to `newAddCmd`), add:\n\n```go\n\taddTo(\"core\", newUpdateCmd(\u0026dir))\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Run the suite to verify it passes**\n\nRun: `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./cmd/kref/ 2\u003e\u00261 | tail -8`\nExpected: PASS.\n\n- [ ] **Step 6: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add cmd/kref/commands.go cmd/kref/main.go cmd/kref/cli_test.go\ngit commit -m \"feat(update): kref update \u003cid\u003e body via --body or stdin\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 4: `kref edit` (interactive `$EDITOR` round-trip)\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `cmd/kref/commands.go` (`newEditCmd`)\n- Modify: `cmd/kref/main.go`\n- Modify: `cmd/kref/cli_test.go`\n\n`edit` materializes the body to a temp file, opens an editor, reads it back, re-derives the title from the body's H1 (only — so a no-H1 body leaves the title unchanged via `store.Update`'s `title==\"\"` semantics), and calls `store.Update`. Editor resolution: `KREF_EDITOR` → `VISUAL` → `EDITOR` → `vi`. The command string is split on whitespace so `\"code --wait\"` works, then the temp path is appended.\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Write the failing CLI spec**\n\nAppend to `cmd/kref/cli_test.go` (uses a tiny editor script that overwrites the file; `os`, `filepath`, `exec`? — only `os`/`filepath` are needed, already imported):\n\n```go\nvar _ = Describe(\"edit command\", func() {\n\tIt(\"opens $EDITOR on the body and saves the result\", func() {\n\t\tdir := gitRepo()\n\t\trun(\"--dir\", dir, \"init\", \"--name\", \"T\", \"--email\", \"t@e.com\")\n\t\tout := run(\"--dir\", dir, \"add\", \"--title\", \"Before\", \"--body\", \"# Before\\n\\nold\", \"--json\")\n\t\tvar a struct {\n\t\t\tID string `json:\"id\"`\n\t\t}\n\t\tExpect(json.Unmarshal([]byte(out), \u0026a)).To(Succeed())\n\n\t\t// A non-interactive \"editor\": a shell script that overwrites the file.\n\t\ted := filepath.Join(GinkgoT().TempDir(), \"ed.sh\")\n\t\tExpect(os.WriteFile(ed, []byte(\"#!/bin/sh\\nprintf '# After\\\\n\\\\nnew text\\\\n' \u003e \\\"$1\\\"\\n\"), 0o755)).To(Succeed())\n\t\tGinkgoT().Setenv(\"KREF_EDITOR\", ed)\n\n\t\tExpect(run(\"--dir\", dir, \"edit\", a.ID)).To(ContainSubstring(\"updated\"))\n\t\tshown := run(\"--dir\", dir, \"show\", a.ID)\n\t\tExpect(shown).To(ContainSubstring(\"new text\"))\n\t\tExpect(shown).To(ContainSubstring(\"After\")) // title re-derived from the new H1\n\t}